      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this heavy, hollow ache right now. It sounds like the world has suddenly shifted under your feet, and the person you knew and loved has vanished into thin air, leaving you with nothing but a shell. That feeling of being a ghost trapped in your own skin is incredibly painful, and it makes total sense that you would wonder if there is even a point to staying when the core of who you were seems to have been erased.\n\nPlease know that while it feels like that version of you is dead, you are not actually a ghost; you are just in a very dark, very quiet room right now. Sometimes, when a big part of us disappears, we feel like the whole building has collapsed, but the foundation is still there, even if we can't see it yet.\n\nYou mentioned that everything you worked for is gone. In the deep, dark tunnels of the goblin world, we often find that when a treasure chest is stolen or a map is torn up, the goblins don't just sit there and die; they start digging for something new, something they didn't even know they were looking for until the old path was blocked. Your current pain is just the goblin equivalent of a",
